      "id": "PopularPost76762",
      "post_content": "In the days of Revised, if you didn't have access to [\\*\\*\\*atrice](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=***atrice), Giant Spider was your best bet as far as flying defense in any green deck. Slap [Regeneration](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Regeneration) on this eight-legged monstrosity, and you had a blocker that could stop just about anything. Its 4 toughness meant it was out of [Lightning Bolt](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lightning Bolt) range, and its relatively low attack power kept it from being [Terror](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Terror)ed very often. The biggest problem with Giant Spider was that it couldn't tangle with the likes of [Serra Angel](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Serra Angel), [Air Elemental](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Air Elemental), or [Sengir Vampire](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sengir Vampire) (the quintessential flyers of their day) without some sort of help. Fortunately, [Giant Growth](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Giant Growth) was usually just one green mana away.",
      "posted_by": "Eppek_the_Goblin",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost76762\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_post\">In the days of Revised, if you didn't have access to <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"***atrice\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=***atrice\">***atrice</a>, Giant Spider was your best bet as far as flying defense in any green deck.  Slap <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Regeneration\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Regeneration\">Regeneration</a> on this eight-legged monstrosity, and you had a blocker that could stop just about anything.  Its 4 toughness meant it was out of <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Lightning Bolt\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lightning Bolt\">Lightning Bolt</a> range, and its relatively low attack power kept it from being <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Terror\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Terror\">Terror</a>ed very often.  The biggest problem with Giant Spider was that it couldn't tangle with the likes of <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Serra Angel\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Serra Angel\">Serra Angel</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Air Elemental\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Air Elemental\">Air Elemental</a>, or <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Sengir Vampire\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sengir Vampire\">Sengir Vampire</a> (the quintessential  flyers of their day) without some sort of help.  Fortunately, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Giant Growth\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Giant Growth\">Giant Growth</a> was usually just one green mana away.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"